results.name: Air Jordan 7 Retro BP 'French Blue'
results.story: Styled for growing feet, the kids’ edition of the Air Jordan 7 Retro 'French Blue' sneaker makes a retro return—sporting the same specs as the 2015 remastered version that updated the OG 2002 colorway. This kids’ sneaker features the same premium leather upper upgrade with University Blue and Flint Grey accents throughout.

results.name: Jordan CP3.IX 'China'
results.story: Chris Paul’s ninth signature sneaker debuted two premier colorways in 2015, including this ‘China Emerald’ iteration. Distinguished by a jagged upper and midsole, the design pairs tonal green colors with black layers and metallic silver details. Signature elements include a dragon on the heel and Chinese characters on the outsole.

results.name: PSNY x Air Jordan 12 Retro 'Friends and Family'
Air Jordan 1 Retro Low BG 'White Varsity Red'
Fragment Design x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Friends and Family'
Air Jordan 1 Retro High PS 'Blake Griffin' PE
Jordan 7 Retro TD Cleat 'Black White'
results.story: The Air Jordan 7 Retro TD Cleats bring a Jordan heritage silhouette to the gridiron. An all-black leather upper features the same layered look as the original, complete with a neoprene interior bootie topped with the AJ7’s signature tongue design. Instead of an Air Sole unit, the midsole features Nike Lunarlon foam, with a 12-cleat outsole configuration underfoot for quick directional changes.

results.name: Air Jordan 13 Retro GT 'Black Hyper Pink'
Air Jordan 1 Mid Nouveau 'Cool Grey'
results.story: Taking cues from various colorways of the Air Jordan line, specifically the AJ11 and AJ9, this exclusive 2014 mid-top updates the iconic Air Jordan 1. The Air Jordan 1 Mid Nouveau features a Cool Grey leather upper with perforations on the toe box and sidewall for breathability. The sneaker also sports a crisp white midsole with responsive cushioning, a contrasting gum rubber outsole, uniquely designed tongue tag, and debossed Wings branding at the ankle.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Gym Red'
results.story: First seen in 1985, the Air Jordan 1 was Michael Jordan's first signature sneaker and remains a classic as more iterations are released. Released in November 2014, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'Gym Red’ takes after its high counterpart with original colors and branding. The Gym Red and black premium upper rests on the classic AJ1 white midsole and a black outsole.

results.name: Slam Dunk x Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Varsity Red'
Jordan Flight 9.5
results.story: The Jordan Flight 9.5 is a hybrid model that takes inspiration from various classic Air Jordan models to create a new off-court silhouette. The mid top’s white leather upper is accented with hits of Cool Grey on the lining and midsole, along with Sport Blue on the extra-tall padded tongue and rubber outsole.

results.name: CP3.VII AE
results.story: The Jordan CP3.VII Artisan Edition is an artistic take on Chris Paul’s signature model. Based in blue, the sneaker’s redesigned Hyperfuse upper is splashed with a multicolor paint splatter print under Dynamic Flywire cables. Underfoot, the textured Podulite tech Phylon midsole is contrasted in white and the herringbone outsole dons complementary colors of Sport Blue and Infrared.

results.name: Jordan Spizike BG 'Cool Grey Vibrant Yellow'
Air Jordan 14 Retro GP 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: Released in 2014, the Air Jordan 14 Retro GP features a design inspired by one of Michael Jordan's favorite car brands, Ferrari. Black and Metallic Dark Grey cover the majority of the shoe's leather and synthetic upper, while Hyper Pink accents appear on the Jordan signature details, lace loops and portions of the midsole and outsole. The low-cut model also features Zoom Air units in the heel and forefoot, a Phylon midsole and herringbone pattern on the outsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 14 Retro TD 'Hyper Pink'
results.story: The Air Jordan 14 Retro Infant features a leather and synthetic upper coated in grey and black with pink and white accents located throughout. Released in 2014, the low-cut sneaker's design draws inspiration from Ferrari and comes with prominent Jumpman branding, an asymmetrical collar and lace loops. Jordan's famous number 23 is displayed on the heel with a white non-marking outsole providing contrast and completing the look.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Brazil'
results.story: Designed by Tinker Hatfield, the Air Jordan 6 was worn by Michael Jordan during the 1990-91 NBA season en route to his first NBA championship ring. Released ahead of the 2014 FIFA World Cup in Brazil, the Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Brazil' features a black nubuck and leather upper with green and yellow accents inspired by the Brazilian flag. The design also includes perforated detailing on the upper and speckled detailing on the midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Low 'White Sport Blue'
Jordan Melo M10
results.story: Jordan Brand’s Melo M10 is the 10th Jumpman sneaker made for Carmelo Anthony. The Jordan 28-inspired sole includes the brand’s signature Flight Plate, while the bright red and black colorway suggests inspiration from the Chicago Bulls. The design is finished off with a chrome heel plate that spells out ‘Melo.’

results.name: Jordan Jumpman Team 1
results.story: Following in the footsteps of iconic Michael Jordan basketball sneakers, the 1997 Nike Jordan Jumpman Team 1 made a comeback with an April 2014 re-release. The classic court shoe is constructed of leather and nubuck overlays with paneled wavy design lines, a look reminiscent of the Air Jordan 12. The upper is reinforced by a textured heel tab and supportive lacing system. Bold Air Jumpman branding completes the retro, yet contemporary look.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid 'Dark Concord'
results.story: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Mid ‘Dark Concord’ features a mixed-material build finished with a straightforward two-tone colorway. The mid-top uses black nylon on the toe box and quarter panel, accented with Dark Concord leather overlays and a black leather Swoosh. Jumpman branding adorns the shoe’s heel panel as well as the tongue tag that graces the lightly padded nylon tongue.

results.name: Jordan Super.Fly 2 PO
results.story: Incorporating the ‘Infrared 23’ color scheme throughout its makeup, the Jordan Super.Fly 2 PO features a black mesh upper with Infrared tones highlighting the tongue, Jumpman branding and laces. Flywire cables on the eyestay complement the inner bootie system, while FlightPlate technology is included in the midsole.

results.name: Jordan Melo M10 Mid 'Black Atomic Mango'
Air Jordan CP3.VII AE
results.story: Chris Paul collaborated with Jordan Brand to continue his Jekyll & Hyde themed colorways. The Air Jordan CP3.VII AE features a mesh-based black upper with multi-color Flywire technology on the laces for support. The sneaker also sports a radio wave-type graphic on the heel dressed in a primarily purple color scheme, a black mesh tongue for breathability and comfort, and a cushioning midsole.

results.name: Air Jordan Future Premium 'Glow'
results.story: The Air Jordan Future Premium 'Glow' features a woven textile upper threaded with reflective 3M stitching. An asymmetrical lacing system curves across the forefoot to lend the shoe a snug fit, while gold tipped laces add contrast. The translucent foam sole, complete with a supportive midfoot shank, glows neon green in the dark. Jumpman branding is debossed on the leather tongue patch.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Retro BP 'Infrared' 2014
results.story: The Air Jordan 6 Retro was first introduced by Michael Jordan en route to his first championship victory in 1991. Resurrected in November 2014 for its 23rd anniversary, this 'Infrared' kids' sneaker is rendered in nubuck with perforated panels. Its innovative tongue is secured by a quick-pull lacing system accented by a Jumpman lace lock. This instant classic sits on an infrared and white sole.

results.name: Jordan Flight 45 High
results.story: Nike revamped the Air Jordan Flight 45 with an all-red color scheme in 2014. Often compared to the Air Jordan 3, the upper construction and midfoot strap pair multiple shades of red. It’s midsole, borrowed from the AJ 3, stands out in contrasting white and black against the tonal look up top.

results.name: Air Jordan 6 Rings 'Elephant'
results.story: Dressed in black, Atomic Orange, New Slate and Wolf Grey, the Air Jordan 6 Rings 'Elephant' was released in January 2014. The silhouette combines elements from the seven Air Jordan models sported by MJ as his Chicago Bulls captured six NBA championships in the 1990s. This iteration comes with Jordan signature detailing and a mesh and leather upper that showcases the iconic elephant print on the overlay. Completing the look is a rubber outsole designed to provide traction on and off the court.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Mid BT 'Black Gym Red'
Air Jordan 12 Retro Gift Pack CB 'Taxi' 2013
Jordan 6 Rings GS 'Hornets'
results.story: This grade school rendition of the Jordan 6 Rings ‘Hornets’ features a colorway inspired by the Charlotte NBA franchise. The primarily black leather construction on the upper sports teal and yellow contrasting throughout. The sneaker also borrows design elements from the Jordan 8, including the dual-strap fastening system and the chenille Jumpman logo seen on the tongue.

results.name: CP3.VII 'Bel Air'
results.story: Chris Paul teamed up with the Jordan Brand to develop the CP3.VII 'Bel Air' revealed in October 2013. Equipped with supportive and flexible Flywire technology and Zoom midsole, the shoe boasts multidirectional traction underfoot. The 1980s-inspired neon colorway accents a black, perforated upper while a 'VIN' number on the sole represents Paul's two children. 'Every time I lace my shoes up,' Paul says, 'I want to feel like I'm taking my family with me.'

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro '89 GS 'Black Fire Red Cement'
Air Jordan 8 Retro GS 'Playoff' 2013
results.story: Dropping in 2013, the Air Jordan 8 Retro GS 'Playoff' 2013 sneaker was released in homage to the 20th anniversary of the 1993 NBA Finals. The children’s interpretation of the adult shoe features a black nubuck upper supported by integrated straps with Nike Air Jordan branding and the number '23,' Michael Jordan’s iconic jersey number with the Chicago Bulls. Its mudguard is adorned with a brushstroke graphic similar to the 1993 ‘Playoff’ shoe.

results.name: Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Black Toe' 2013 Sample
Air Jordan 9 'Photo Blue' Black Bottom
results.story: The original ‘Photo Blue’ edition of the Air Jordan 9, which dropped in 2012, featured a white outsole. However, an alleged factory error resulted in pairs of the shoe being produced with a black outsole. Not wanting to scrap the unexpected colorway, Nike repurposed it as the ‘Black Bottom’ and released it a year later on Nike.com. Whether a true story or not, both ‘Photo Blue’ AJ9s pair a black upper with blue accents, but only this one boasts a black bottom.

results.name: Jordan Melo M9 'Knicks'
results.story: Carmelo Anthony’s ninth signature shoe with Jordan brand sports the New York Knicks team colors, featuring a combination of smooth and patent leather paneling throughout the upper, while the mesh tongue promotes breathability. The cross-weave overlays on the side panels work themselves up from the midsole to the eyelets to provide lateral forefoot support, and the inner bootie system is included for a personalized fit.

results.name: Jordan CP3.VI AE 'Squadron Green'
results.story: Jordan Brand released a fresh Artisan Edition of the CP3. The Jordan CP3.VI AE 'Squadron Green' features a mesh-based upper in an all-over Squadron Green color scheme for a military-inspired look. The sneaker also boasts fin-like details along the side wall and heel in patent leather, a breathable wrap-around tongue for an easy and comfortable fit, the classic Jumpman logo in black at the heel side, and a contrasting white traction-forward outsole.

results.name: Jordan Flight Luminary 'Cool Grey Bright Citrus'
Air Jordan 8 Retro 'Bugs Bunny' 2013
results.story: Jordan Brand celebrated the 20th anniversary of the Air Jordan 8 with a retro of the iconic 1993 home colorway worn by Michael Jordan during the 1992-1993 NBA season. Released in April 2013, the sneaker has been nicknamed the 'Bugs Bunny' after the 1990s commercial campaign starring MJ and the Looney Tunes character.

results.name: CP3.VII AE
results.story: Chris Paul’s third signature sneaker, the Jordan CP3.VI AE (Artisan Edition), debuted three new colorways in 2013 including this Neo Turquoise and black option. The futuristic silhouette features a black-based leather and mesh combination upper with contrast stitching and blue accents at the eyelets, liner, heel tab, and mini Jumpman logos. Underfoot, the blue hue also highlights Podulon tech which delivers area-specific comfort and responsiveness.

results.name: Jordan CP3.VI AE 'Sport Red Game Royal'
